The four TAhE cmavo are differentiated as follows: ru'icovers the entirety of the interval,
ru'i di'icovers the parts of the interval which are systematically spaced subintervals;
di'i na'ocovers part of the interval, but exactly which part is determined by context;
na'o ta'ecovers part of the interval, selected with reference to the behavior of the actor (who often, but not always, appears in the x1 place of the bridi).

